\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Postmodernism attmepts to throw knowledge into a hole. Once done, anything goes. My interpretation, is as good as yours. This results in the degradation of a civil society. How can one punish or exert control? How can one justify any action which might enforce one interpretation of reality over another? There can be no justification if everyone is interpreting for themselves. In such a world, there is only raw, cynical power.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Get to an understanding of knowledge which knocks it off its pedestal, while also avoiding the trap of falling into a postmodern hole. Useful, because knowledge is power, and if we have a more refined understand of what knowledge actually is, we\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ll be all the more powerful.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 There is reality}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Start with the beginning. Our minds are embodied. This means there is a hard boundary between our minds and the environment. Consequently, it must invent it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The problem of scale.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Numbers are not real, a symptom of a partial view.}}